      "id": "sybil_9_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_9",
      "description": "This 2004 Porsche 911 Carrera (996.2) is a mechanically sound example of the final evolution of the 996 chassis. At its heart is the 3.6L naturally aspirated M96 flat-six, featuring VarioCam Plus for optimized torque across the rev range. The engine is mated to a Getrag G96 6-speed manual transaxle, providing crisp engagement and a direct connection to the rear-wheel-drive layout. The suspension maintains its factory-spec MacPherson struts up front and a sophisticated five-arm multi-link setup in the rear, offering excellent lateral stability and turn-in precision. Noteworthy maintenance includes a documented IMS bearing retrofit and a reinforced cooling system with a high-flow water pump. While the bodywork shows light evidence of road use, the hydraulic steering remains communicative and the four-piston Monobloc calipers provide firm, fade-resistant braking. This is a robust, driver-focused machine ready for the twisties.",
